				\begin{document}$${{{{\rm{CATE}}}}}=\int\,Yp(Y| X,T=1)\,{{{{\rm{d}}}}}Y-\int\,Yp(Y| X,T=0)\,{{{{\rm{d}}}}}Y,$$\end{document}CATE=∫Yp(Y∣X,T=1)dY−∫Yp(Y∣X,T=0)dY,where p(Y ∣X, T = 1) and p(Y ∣X, T = 0) are the conditional probability distribution of Y given X for the treated and control groups. If we can estimate p(Y ∣X, T = 1) ≈ qT(Y ∣X) and p(Y ∣X, T = 0) ≈ qC(Y∣X) and sample from them, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
